There is a `if` statement catching the case of `None` value.
```python
if rss_count is None:
    response['full_text'] = self.py3.safe_format(
        self.format, {'unseen': self._cached}
    )
    response['color'] = self.py3.COLOR_ERROR or self.py3.COLOR_BAD
```

To reduce complexity, can we relocate the fallbacks or `if` checks to be within the `register_unregister` call and always use `with`?

```python
def lint(content, filepath=None, custom_directives=None, custom_roles=None):
    with ignores.register_unregister_ignores(custom_directives, custom_roles):
        return _lint(content, filepath=filepath)
```

not necessarily. it is the desc passed directly to CreateMKLDNNMem. and it could be the desc provided by the the operator.

``
mkldnn::sum::primitive_desc pdesc(scales, in_pds);
auto mem = CreateMKLDNNMem(out_data, pdesc.dst_primitive_desc(), req, &inputs[0]);
``

I would rename this test to `test_build_and_get_cluster_app_bootstrap_script_inlined` and additionally check if subsequent getting of the app (with `dx get app-xxxx`) unpacks the app configuration into `dxapp.json` so that we can later build the app again with `dx build`, e.g.:

```
+                            "aws:us-east-1": {
+                                "systemRequirements": {
+                                    "cluster_1": {
+                                        "instanceType": "mem2_hdd2_x1",
+                                        "clusterSpec": {"type": "spark",
+                                                                    "version": "2.2.0",
+                                                                    "initialInstanceCount": 5,
+                                                                    "bootstrapScript": "clusterBootstrap.py"}
+                                                                    }
+                                    "cluster_2": {
+                                        "instanceType": "mem2_hdd2_x4",
+                                        "clusterSpec": <as above>
+                                    }
+                                }
+                            }}
```

The code for unpaking the app with `dx get` is here: https://github.com/dnanexus/dx-toolkit/blob/master/src/python/dxpy/utils/executable_unbuilder.py#L238

Getting needs to result in dxapp.json whose specification is here: https://wiki.dnanexus.com/dxapp.json

Also is the file `clusterBootstrap.py` region-specific or the same for all regions?

This should just be:
```
def parse_conan_stdout_for_pkg_sha(self, stdout):
  pkg_spec_escaped = re.escape(self.pkg_spec)
  pkg_spec_pattern = re.compile('^{}:(.*)$'.format(pkg_spec_escaped), flags=re.MULTILINE)
  return pkg_spec_pattern.search(stdout).group(1)

